{
  "texts": [
    "Frames with a P Gesture value below the predetermined threshold are discarded as they are considered not to contain any gesture.",
    "From the remaining frames, the frame closest to the radar, determined by the nearest R Gesture index, is identified as F Gesture, indicating the frame where the hand performed the gesture and was closest to the radar.To extract range information, an FFT is applied to the preprocessed and filtered data along the fast-time dimension [13].",
    "This allows for the identification of specific frequency components associated with target reflections.",
    "Following these steps, the range information (R) is subjected to extra analysis.",
    "In this regard, the absolute values of the mean along both antennas and slow-time dimensions are computed, yielding the range profile (R Profile)."
  ]
}